The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine comprehension, which are both subfields of computer science. The paper specifically deals with Chinese reading comprehension, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed neural network architecture also involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed model, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval, as it deals with understanding and answering questions based on textual data (cs.IR).
